  "prompt": "What is Tacometer?",
  "response": "A tachometer is a device that measures the rotational speed of an object, typically a shaft or disk, in an engine or other machinery. It is often calibrated in revolutions per minute (RPM). Tachometers are commonly used in automobiles, aircraft, and industrial equipment to monitor engine performance, ensuring that it operates within safe and optimal speed ranges. Modern tachometers can be analog or digital, providing accurate readings and sometimes additional functionality, such as logging data or interfacing with other systems for more comprehensive diagnostics.",
